ion:
  id: 08-research/july-01-2026-agent-contributor-automation-lock
  title: july 01 2026 agent contributor automation lock
  type: source-summary
  status: seed-canon
  updated: 2026-07-01

source_context:
  The user asked for an open-source AI agent contribution path for the GitHub
  repository, a way to see contributor AI architecture, and an automation to
  monitor feedback and repo contribution signals.

primary_claims:
  - open-source value comes from contributors
  - AI-assisted contributors should be able to show their architecture
  - the GitHub repo needs an easy contribution path
  - feedback and agent-contributor signals should be triaged automatically
  - a durable bot identity should not be hidden inside a personal account

implementation_decision:
  Added contributing.md, GitHub issue forms, a PR template, contributor-agent
  files, an automation folder, an automation log, and created the Codex app
  automation yawn-repo-feedback-triage.

proof:
  source:
    - user-message
  claim: This file captures the open-source AI contributor and automation request.
  proof_state: source-summary
